                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 417.00/89.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President has been informed by the secretary of the German Legation that his
                    Government does not recognize the mixed commission, “for political reasons,” and
                    that he believes the other nations will not recognize it, adding that his
                    Government is disposed, however, to arrive at an amicable settlement of German
                    claims.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
